						<summary>

						<p>Stone lying in the varandah of the school. </p>						

						<p>There are three slabs, one of which contains the names of some goddesses such as Mahishāsuramardini.</p>						

						<p>Another is a fragmentary record which mentions [Ka]nnaradēva. The third record refers to the date Śaka 1242 (1320 A.D.) and mentions a few names ending with <hi rend="italic">dēva.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
